Nation Nyoka, News24An abandoned baby reaches out to mobiles above its crib at the Door of Hope in Johannesburg. (Denis Farrell, AP, file) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Johannesburg - The woman who allegedly abandoned her baby girl in the toilet of the Key West mall in Krugersdorp has been arrested, police have said.The 27-year-old woman, an employee at the mall, was arrested at work on Wednesday afternoon, Captain Appel Ernst said in a statement.She will appear in the Krugersdorp Magistrate's Court on a charge of child abandonment on Friday.Family Violence, Child Protection and Sexual Offences Investigations commander, Lieutenant-Colonel Kathy Segotta, said the baby was doing well.A shopper found the baby in the toilets on Friday, May 5, the mall's marketing manager Michelle Papastefanou said.She was taken to Dr Yusuf Dadoo Hospital.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.